SIMPLE: coronary_cushion
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Coronary cushion
<hw>Coronary cushion</hw>. <def>A cushionlike band of vascular tissue at
the upper border of the wall of the hoof of the horse and allied
animals. It takes an important part in the secretion of the horny
walls.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coronary thrombosis</ent>⟦br⟧
